  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (edge-case coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results span the nominal 2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM operating envelope; high-shear-stress regions at impeller tip clearance and volute cutwater, and low-flow stall conditions explicitly named in the COU, are stated to have been studied separately but no linked evidence is provided.",
